text: The purple and orange leaf frog (Calllimedusa duellmani) is a frog that lives in Peru. Scientists have only seen it in one place. People have seen this frog between 1,850 and 1,910 meters above sea level. This frog lives in cloud forests. The female frog finds a leaf over water and folds it. She lays her eggs in the fold. When the eggs hatch, the tadpoles fall into the water. ==References== Category:Frogs of South America
title: Callimedusa duellmani
